FuncDef:
The web-auth-server enable command enables web authentication.
The undo web-auth-server enable command disables web authentication.
By default, web authentication is disabled.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
The web-auth-server enable command can be used to enable web authentication.
Configuration Impact
After web authentication is disabled, users cannot be authenticated in web authentication mode.
Follow-up Procedure
If web authentication is enabled, you need to configure a web server.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
